<h1 style="margin-bottom:0px;">Network Load Balancer</h1><div class="f14 metric" style="color:#656668;display:flex;"><img src="/assets/images/calendar.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="updateDate">&nbsp; Updated on 26/06/2019</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="/assets/images/updated.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="readTime">&nbsp; 1 minute to read</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><br><div class="mw-parser-output"><p>AWS Network Load Balancer distributes incoming TCP traffic across multiple EC2 instances that are working as masters and workers. This increases the availability of CDF and the suite.  Network Load Balancer is used only for network traffic within the VPC. 
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="_Create_Network_Load_Balancer">&nbsp;Create Network Load Balancer</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/NLoBalOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=1" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: &nbsp;Create Network Load Balancer">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/NLoBalOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: &nbsp;Create Network Load Balancer">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>To create a Network Load Balancer, follow these steps:
</p>
<ol><li>Click <b>Create Load Balancer</b> from AWS console:  <a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://console.aws.amazon.com/ec2/v2/home#LoadBalancers">https://console.aws.amazon.com/ec2/v2/home#LoadBalancers</a></li>
<li>Select <b>Network Load Balancer</b> and click <b>Create</b>.</li>
<li>Complete <b>Step 1 Configure Load Balancer</b>:
<ul><li>In the <b>Basic Configuration</b> section, select <b>internal</b> for <b>Scheme</b>.</li>
<li>In the <b>Listeners</b> section,  add listeners for the 4 Target Groups  with <b>Protocol</b> TCP and <b>Ports</b> 2380, 4001, 8200, and 8443 respectively.</li>
<li>In the <b>Availability Zones</b> section, associate the 3 Availability Zones, with their private subnet selected. <a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge 2019.02NLB4.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/9/9e/OpsBridge_2019.02NLB4.jpg" width="1053" height="334" data-file-width="1053" data-file-height="334"></a></li></ul></li>
<li>In <b>Step 2 Config Routing</b>, associate the Target Groups created previously. <a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge 2019.02NLB5.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/a/a2/OpsBridge_2019.02NLB5.jpg" width="932" height="695" data-file-width="932" data-file-height="695"></a></li></ol>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="_Configure_Network_Load_Balancer">&nbsp;Configure Network Load Balancer</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/NLoBalOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=2" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: &nbsp;Configure Network Load Balancer">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/NLoBalOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: &nbsp;Configure Network Load Balancer">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ol><li>After creating the Network Load Balancer, configure load balancer listeners to associate with the right TCP Target Groups.  <a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge 2019.02NLB6.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/9/9d/OpsBridge_2019.02NLB6.jpg" width="531" height="455" data-file-width="531" data-file-height="455"></a></li>
<li>Enable the <b>Cross-Zone Load Balancing</b> attribute on the <b>Description</b> page of the load balancer. <a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02NlB8.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/3/39/OpsBridge2019.02NlB8.jpg" width="723" height="565" data-file-width="723" data-file-height="565"></a></li></ol>
<div class="Admonition_Note"><span class="autonumber">Note </span>For more information about Network Load Balancer, see:
<p><a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/elasticloadbalancing/latest/network/network-load-balancers.html">https://docs.aws.amazon.com/elasticloadbalancing/latest/network/network-load-balancers.html</a>
</p>
</div>
<ol><li class="mw-empty-elt"></li></ol>
<p><br>
